{"questionId":"13123","questionHtml":"<p>Write down two transformations that will transform the graph of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = v\\left( t \\right)\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>v</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>t</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> onto the graph of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = i\\left( t \\right)\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>i</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>t</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>stretch parallel to the <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n</math></span>-axis (with <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span>-axis invariant), scale factor&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{2}{3}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n    <mn>3</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>translation of&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  { - 0.003} \\\\   0  \\end{array}} \\right)\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mn>0.003</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>0</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; (shift to the left by 0.003) &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Can be done in either order.</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"13123","referenceCode":"19M.2.AHL.TZ1.H_10b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Write down two transformations that will transform the graph of y = v ( t ) onto the graph of y = i ( t ) .","paper":"2","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.11—Definite integrals, areas under curve onto x-axis and areas between curves","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.7—Circular functions: graphs, composites, transformations","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.11—Transformation of functions"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}